[SN]TITLE[SN]
Everton shooting: Two more arrests in murder investigation

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A further two people have been arrested in connection with the fatal shooting of a man in Liverpool.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Mark Hillman, 26, was shot twice in the back and found on a pavement in Lloyd Close, Everton, on 27 April.
A 19-year-old from Anfield has been arrested on suspicion of conspiracy to commit murder.
A woman, 43, also from Anfield, was held on suspicion of assisting an offender. Both have now been bailed pending further inquiries.
Three people previously arrested over Mr Hillman's death have also been released on bail.
